(43, 14, 24, 43, 7, 16, 16, NULL, 'Connection of Jesus'' Doctrine', 'Both passages emphasize that Jesus'' teachings are not his own but come from the Father. This connection highlights the divine authority behind Jesus'' words.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 14, 24, 43, 14, 10, 10, 'the word which ye hear is not mine', 'Connection of Divine Authority', 'Both passages emphasize that the words spoken by Jesus are not his own but come from the Father. This connection highlights the unity between Jesus and the Father in their teachings and actions.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 14, 24, 40, 25, 41, 46, 'keepeth not my sayings', 'Connection of Love and Action', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of actions reflecting one''s love for Christ. In John 14:24, not keeping His sayings indicates a lack of love, while Matthew 25:41-46 illustrates that failing to care for others shows a failure to recognize Christ''s teachings.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 14, 24, 62, 3, 16, 20, 'loveth me not keepeth not my sayings', 'Love and Action Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of love manifested through actions. John 14:24 highlights obedience to God''s word as a sign of love, while 1 John 3:16-20 stresses laying down one''s life and showing compassion as expressions of that love.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 14, 24, 47, 8, 8, 9, 'loveth me not keepeth not my sayings', 'Love and Sacrifice Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of love demonstrated through actions. In John 14:24, love is shown by keeping the sayings of Jesus, while 2 Corinthians 8:8-9 illustrates love through the sacrificial act of Christ''s poverty for others'' benefit.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 14, 24, 40, 19, 21, 21, 'keepeth not my sayings', 'Love and Obedience Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of obedience to Jesus'' teachings. In John 14:24, not keeping His sayings indicates a lack of love, while Matthew 19:21 emphasizes following Jesus through action, such as selling possessions and helping the poor.', 'theme', 0.3, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 14, 25, 43, 17, 6, 8, 'These things have I spoken unto you', 'Connection of Words and Revelation', 'Both passages emphasize the transmission of words from Jesus to his followers. In John 14:25, Jesus speaks to them while present, and in John 17:6-8, he reflects on how they have received those words and recognized his divine origin.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 14, 25, 43, 13, 19, 19, NULL, 'Connection of Foreknowledge and Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of foretelling events to strengthen belief. In John 14:25, the speaker indicates prior communication, while John 13:19 highlights the purpose of foretelling to affirm identity.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 14, 25, 43, 16, 12, 12, 'These things have I spoken unto you', 'Teaching and Understanding Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the limitation of the disciples'' understanding. In John 14:25, Jesus acknowledges His current teaching, while in John 16:12, He indicates there are more teachings they cannot yet comprehend.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 14, 25, 43, 14, 29, 29, 'These things have I spoken unto you', 'Connection of Foretelling and Belief', 'This connection highlights the theme of Jesus preparing His disciples for future events. Both passages emphasize His intention to strengthen their belief through His teachings and foretelling.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 14, 25, 43, 15, 11, 11, 'These things have I spoken unto you', 'Connection of Joy and Teaching', 'Both passages emphasize the act of speaking to the disciples. The first verse indicates that Jesus spoke while present, and the second highlights the purpose of His words to ensure joy remains and is full.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 14, 25, 43, 16, 1, 4, 'These things have I spoken unto you', 'Connection of Jesus'' Teachings', 'Both passages emphasize the teachings of Jesus as a preparation for future challenges. The phrase ''These things have I spoken unto you'' links the warnings in John 16 to the prior teachings in John 14.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 14, 26, 43, 15, 26, 26, 'the Comforter', 'Connection of the Comforter', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Comforter, identified as the Holy Ghost, in teaching and testifying about Jesus. The Comforter is sent by the Father in both instances, highlighting a consistent theme of divine guidance.', 'theme', 0.8739999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 14, 26, 43, 14, 16, 16, 'the Comforter', 'Connection of the Comforter', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Comforter, identified as the Holy Ghost, sent by the Father. They highlight the Comforter''s purpose to teach and abide with believers.', 'theme', 0.825, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 14, 26, 62, 2, 27, 27, 'he shall teach you all things', 'Teaching by the Holy Spirit', 'This connection highlights the role of the Holy Spirit in teaching believers. Both passages emphasize that the Holy Spirit will teach and remind them of all things.', 'theme', 0.7549999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 14, 26, 46, 2, 10, 13, NULL, 'Role of the Holy Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Holy Spirit in teaching and revealing divine truths. John 14:26 speaks of the Holy Spirit teaching and bringing remembrance, while 1 Corinthians 2:10-13 highlights the Spirit''s role in revealing the deep things of God.', 'theme', 0.734, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 14, 26, 62, 2, 20, 20, 'he shall teach you all things', 'Connection of Divine Teaching', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Holy Spirit in imparting knowledge and understanding to believers. John 14:26 speaks of the Holy Spirit teaching and reminding, while 1 John 2:20 asserts that believers have an unction that grants them knowledge.', 'theme', 0.566, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 14, 26, 45, 15, 13, 13, 'Holy Ghost', 'Connection of the Holy Ghost', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Holy Ghost in providing guidance and hope. John 14:26 speaks of the Holy Ghost teaching and reminding believers, while Romans 15:13 highlights the Holy Ghost''s power in filling believers with joy and hope.', 'theme', 0.503, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 14, 26, 49, 1, 17, 17, 'he shall teach you all things', 'Connection of Wisdom and Teaching', 'This connection highlights the role of the Holy Spirit in imparting wisdom and knowledge. Both passages emphasize the teaching and revelation that comes from God through the Spirit.', 'theme', 0.496, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 14, 27, 23, 41, 10, 10, 'Let not your heart be troubled', 'Connection of Divine Peace and Strength', 'Both passages emphasize the reassurance against fear. John 14:27 speaks of peace, while Isaiah 41:10 offers strength and support from God, highlighting a divine presence that alleviates anxiety.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 14, 27, 43, 16, 33, 33, 'peace I leave with you', 'Connection of Peace in John', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of peace that Jesus offers. In John 14:27, He states, ''Peace I leave with you,'' while in John 16:33, He reiterates that in Him, believers might have peace despite tribulation.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 14, 27, 50, 4, 7, 7, 'peace I leave with you', 'Connection of Divine Peace', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of peace given by God. John 14:27 speaks of ''my peace'' while Philippians 4:7 refers to ''the peace of God,'' highlighting a divine source of tranquility that transcends worldly understanding.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 14, 27, 53, 3, 16, 16, 'peace I leave with you', 'Connection of Peace in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of peace given by the Lord. John 14:27 speaks of Jesus'' peace, while 2 Thessalonians 3:16 mentions the Lord of peace providing peace always.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 14, 27, 51, 3, 15, 15, 'peace I leave with you', 'Connection of Peace in Scripture', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of peace given by God. John 14:27 speaks of the peace Jesus provides, while Colossians 3:15 encourages believers to let the peace of God rule in their hearts.', 'theme', 0.986, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 14, 27, 55, 1, 7, 7, 'Let not your heart be troubled', 'Connection of Peace and Fear', 'Both passages emphasize the absence of fear and the provision of peace. John 14:27 speaks of peace that alleviates troubled hearts, while 2 Timothy 1:7 states that God does not give a spirit of fear.', 'theme', 0.7969999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 14, 27, 45, 15, 13, 13, 'peace I leave with you', 'Connection of Peace and Hope', 'Both passages emphasize the themes of peace and hope. John 14:27 speaks of peace given by Jesus, while Romans 15:13 mentions being filled with joy and peace in believing, linking the concepts of divine peace and hope.', 'theme', 0.7689999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 14, 28, 43, 10, 29, 30, 'my Father is greater than I', 'Relationship Between Father and Son', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between Jesus and the Father. John 14:28 highlights the Father''s greater status, while John 10:30 asserts their unity, illustrating the complexity of their relationship.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 14, 28, 46, 15, 24, 28, 'my Father is greater than I', 'Authority and Submission to God', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between Jesus and the Father, highlighting that Jesus acknowledges the Father''s greater authority. In 1 Corinthians, it is stated that the Son will be subject to the Father after all things are subdued, reflecting the same theme of hierarchy and submission found in John.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
